05/04/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- A Tirana court barred Jordanian national Hamzeh Abu Rayyan from the leaving the country Wednesday (April 4th) until an investigation into possible terrorist connections is completed. 
Rayyan is suspected of laundering money on behalf of a group connected with al-Qaeda.
In other news Wednesday, Parliament's media committee asked the National Radio and Television Commission to submit a report on the media in light of recent changes in ownership of some TV stations. 
The request followed claims of media corruption last week by Prime Minister Sali Berisha. 
The opposition, while sceptical about Berisha's motives, agreed on the need for complete transparency regarding media ownership and financing. 
(Albanian News, Shekulli - 05/04/07; AFP, A1 TV - 04/04/07)
